{
  "doc_id": "16038",
  "text": "Another approach to improve energy efficiency of BEVs is the introduction of multi-speed transmissions. Traditionally, unlike in the powertrain of combustion engines, only a single reduction gear was used for BEVs [CITATION_1] . As a result, the operating point of the motor cannot be adjusted for given vehicle speed and acceleration command. However, in recent years, multi-speed transmissions for BEVs, i.e., 2-4 speed transmissions, have been considered [CITATION_2] - [CITATION_3] to achieve further energy efficiency improvement.",
